BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Press Democrat": "https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops"}
X-SOURCE-ID:pressdemocrat
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T120000
UID:260219oJry11JQnEqH-MstUXHzlA
DESCRIPTION:**Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challe
 nge" (online).** \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\n**Only
  $5**\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\n***M
 arch Month of Flowers* Challenge** is here to give you a creative outlet
 \, some structure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a b
 rush\, pen\, or pencil (thread\, clay\, fabric…)\, your brain gets a res
 t and becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more 
 alive\; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Y
 our intuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curios
 ity grows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you fi
 nd the freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Petaluma Arts Center": "https://petalumaartscenter.org/events-exhibitions/livefiguredrawing-swj9s"}
X-SOURCE-ID:petaluma_arts_center
SUMMARY:Weekly Live Figure Drawing 
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T010000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T040000
UID:8766f47611e07e45f97857449e1bda8f@petalumaartscenter.org
DESCRIPTION:Live Figure Drawing Every Monday from 6:00pm-9:00pm. This is a
 n uninstructed drop-in session with different models rotating through\, us
 ually in the nude (although sometimes with costumes and props). Poses typi
 cally range from 2 minutes to 20 minutes\, increasing in length. Please br
 ing your own supplies. Tables and chairs will be provided. A limited numbe
 r of tables\, easels\, and drawing horses are available on a first-come/fi
 rst-serve basis. Feel free to bring your own easel or small table if you w
 ould like to as well. Admission at the door is $20. $15 for PAC members &a
