DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSession 1: Tuesdays\, January 27 – February 17\,
  2026 6:00 PM – 9:00 PM Session 2: Tuesdays\, February 24 – March 17\,
  2026 6:00 PM – 9:00 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nIntermediate\n\nEvent Cat
 egory: Ceramics\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n17\\+\n\nSingle Session – 4 weeks: $140
  Registration Fee $30 Materials Fee $170 Total Registration Fee\n\nBoth Se
 ssions – 8 weeks: $265 Registration Fee $30 Materials Fee $295 Total Reg
 istration Fee\n\nWork independently on personal projects with the direct s
 upport of an instructor by your side in this Independent Projects Class wi
 th Amy Hamley.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nThis session has been split into 2\
 , 4 week sessions – you can enroll in each session independently or enro
 ll in both as a package deal!This course is for students interested in exp
 loring both wheel throwing AND handbuilding\, and the combination of both 
 in one class! Learn from Hamley’s years of expertise in the field and en
 joy creating handbuilt\, thrown\, and altered forms. Amy caters each sylla
 bus closely to her group of students\, ensuring that every project fits th
 e desires of participants. This course encourages folks to work on indepen
 dent projects in the class\, receiving one on one support from Amy through
 out the time. This course will include demos\, exercises\, and utilize a v
 ariety of methods to achieve the desired goal for each student. Some proje
 cts may include wheel thrown vases with altered adornments\, best practice
 s for slump and hump molds\, and more.\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nA
 ll Silver Memberships and above receive 10% off the registration cost for 
 any class purchase over $40. Materials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome 
 a member today and find community\, connection\, and creativity.\n\nLocati
 on\n\nRoom 117\, Ceramics Studio
