DESCRIPTION:Meets the fourth Thursday of the month from 2-3 pm. Pick up a 
 copy of each month's book at the Sonoma Valley Branch while supplies last.
  Then\, please come and discuss it with us. We look forward to seeing you!
  Book Club titles and dates are subject to change. For up to date informat
 ion visit: sonomalibrary.org/bookclubs 2026 Schedule January 15 - The Wide
  Wide Sea by Hampton Sides February 19 - Martyr! by Kaveh Akbar March 19 -
  Roses\, in the Mouth of a Lion by Bushra Rehman April 16 - Family Lore by
  Elizabeth Acevedo May 21 - The Heaven & Earth Grocery Store by James McBr
 ide June 18 - Eager by Ben Goldfarb July 16 - A Fever in the Heartland by 
 Timothy Egan August 20 - James by Percival Everett September 17 - Pedro P
 áramo by Juan Rulfo October 15 - The Anxious Generation by Jonathan Haidt
  November 19 - The Kamogawa Food Detectives by Hisashi Kashiwai December 1
