DESCRIPTION:Join us for a monthly Tabletop Role-playing Game Club \\(TTRPG
 \\) on the third Thursday of every month from 4-5pm. For Tweens and Teens 
 \\(grades 4-12\\) Play TTRPG games like D&D \\(Dungeons and Dragons\\) and
  a variety of TTRPGs like Library Cats and Hero Quest. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 ~~~~~~~~~~ Games will be run by a variety of Librarian and Teen DMs. Bring
  your own already-made character sheet or choose from one of our premade c
 haracters \\(https://dndadventureclub.com/resources/characters\\). Players
  are encouraged to bring their dice\, books\, miniatures\, etc. No persona
 l materials are needed to play\, but attendees are encouraged to bring the
 ir supplies if they own them. Please be on time and ready to play. Session
 s are about 30-45 minutes. Please register for this program so we have an 
 estimate for group sizes and so that we can email notifications about this
  program. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Looking for DMs! Are you a 13-18 and
  interested in running a game for tweens and teens? Email us at kdargeou@s
 onomalibrary.org ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Tabletop roleplaying games \
 \(TTRPGs\\) empower students to be creative and solve problems as a team.
LOCATION:Sonoma Valley Regional Library
