SUMMARY: Acoustic Saturday at Adobe Road Winery featuring Anthony Presti
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special Saturday acoustic live music set at Ado
 be Road Winery in downtown Petaluma. Sip on award-winning wines while enj
 oying talented local musicians in a warm and inviting atmosphere. Choose 
 from wines by the glass or bottle to discover new favorites. Reserve your
  spot on Tock https://www.exploretock.com/adoberoadwines/ and make it a m
 emorable night of great music\, fine wine\, and good company!\n\nAbout An
 thony Presti\n\nSinger/Songwriter\, Anthony Presti\, grew up in Seattle i
 n the 90’s during a thriving grunge movement\, obsessing over bands like 
 Nirvana and Pearl Jam while being exposed to bands like the Grateful Dead
  and Jethro Tull by his uncles\, who taught him the significance of music
 . He ended up moving to Sonoma County as a teenager\, where punk dominate
 d the mainstream. After playing in a hardcore band for a number of years\
 , Presti discovered an affinity for acoustic guitar and folk songwriting 
 and eventually settled in San Francisco where he formed his backing band\
 , The Tusslers.\n\nPresti’s style encompasses folk nuances mixed with the
  inspirations of his rock upbringing. He’s released two full length album
 s\, including his second record in 2017\, Existentialism\, recorded at Jo
 hn Vanderslice’s Tiny Telephone Studios and is currently working on his l
 atest release due out this year\, Different Places\, at Hyde Street Studi
 os.
CATEGORIES:music,live-music,wine,winery
