SUMMARY:Happy Hour Crafts
DESCRIPTION:The Rebel Craft Collective\nWine + tasty snacks + your latest 
 project and a friendly group of likeminded crafters... what better way to 
 unwind? Come join us!\n\nThis is a relaxed\, drop-in-friendly event. Come 
 when you can\, leave when you must. Newcomers and occasional-comers are al
 ways welcome!\n\n**What do we mean by “crafts”?**\nWhatever “craft
 ” means to you! And whatever is portable enough to bring to a wine bar. 
 Knitting\, crochet\, and other fiber arts are most common\, but we have al
 so warmly welcomed people who sketch\, color\, embroider\, bead\, and more
 . If your craft isn’t portable\, we will happily ooh and aah over photos
  of your work-in-progress\, or chat about your plans for your next project
 .\n\n**Health & Safety**\nMasks are very welcome\, and nobody will pressur
 e you to eat or drink. If the weather is nice\, we will try to sit outside
 . If you aren’t eating/drinking during the event\, please consider order
 ing some of La Dolce Vita’s delicious food to-go\, in order to help supp
 ort our gracious\, long-time venue.\n\n**Parking**\nParking in downtown Pe
 taluma is free\, but street parking has a strictly enforced 2 hour limit u
 ntil 6pm. To park for longer\, try the nearest garage:\n\n* The Second Str
 eet Garage entrance is located on C Street between First and Second Street
 s. It's all day parking on every level and a short walk to La Dolce Vita.\
 n\n**Ages**\nIt's a wine bar\, so this event is for adult crafters (though
  you're certainly not required to drink wine!). We’re okay with babes-in
 -arms if you are\, but this is not the right setting for wee crafters who 
 are moving about on their own.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-rebel-craft-collective/events/313
 260331/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260208T041629Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260208T041629Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"The Big Easy": "https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/secret-song-club-presents-chris-hanlin-amie-penwell/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bigeasy
X-SOURCE:The Big Easy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T220000
DTSTAMP:20260308T185710
CREATED:20260305T020633Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260305T020633Z
UID:10002567-1774551600-1774562400@bigeasypetaluma.com
SUMMARY:Secret Song Club presents Chris Hanlin + Amie Penwell
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the first in a monthly series showcasing Bay Area songwriters. The night starts with an open mic followed by featured artists Chris Hanlin and Amie Penwell. Free entry\, no cover. Tip jar donations for Chris and Amie are welcomed. Sign up to play the open mic at drew@insidelands.org \nChris Hanlin is an American singer\, multi instrumentalist\, and songwriter. Chris was born in Indiana and even though he has called California home for many decades\, his roots in the American Midwest shine through his soulful songs and thought provoking lyrics. Chris has written\, performed\, and recorded many styles of music throughout his career. Whenever Chris starts to sing he pours his heart into every line sung and every note played. Chris Hanlin is a true singer songwriter. \nAmie’s music walks a fine line between piano-driven pop\, soul and country while maintaining an alternative aesthetic which allows her the freedom to mold\, shape\, bend and blend the various styles which influence her the most\, joining the likes of Annie Lennox and Aimee Mann\, and Peter Gabriel\, \n“I’ve spent the last few years working on a collection of songs that came out of conversations I had\, and experiences I’ve shared\, with women of diverse ethnic\, economic and religious backgrounds\,” Amie says. “With the help of my collaborators\, that collection has become my new record\, Windows. It’s an intimate\, firsthand look into the lives of nine women on nine different journeys. Each song is a portrait of individual and collective exploration through acceptance\, power\, will\, humility\, denial\, willingness\, faith\, surrender\, and freedom.” \nAmie’s underground hit single\, “Mercy\,” was featured in the award-winning 2012 documentary\, The Eyes of Thailand\, which was narrated by Ashley Judd. In 2013\, my EP Under City Lights was featured on Season 2 of Web series “Bloomers” and The Ask BonBon Show. In 2015\, she was a semi-finalist in the International Songwriting Contest (ISC) in the Adult Album Alternative category for her song “Dogfight On The Moon”. In 2016\, her song “Somewhere The Sky Is Blue” with Grammy Award-winning Producer Ricky Kej\, in the Dominica Scorsese film Almost Paris\, her song Unstoppable made it into the Mary Janes The Women of Weed as it’s credits song. Amie is currently writing and recording with Vicente Rodriguez (Chuck Prophet).
URL:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/secret-song-club-presents-chris-hanlin-amie-penwell/
LOCATION:The Big Easy\, 128 American Alley\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
CATEGORIES:Americana,Indie-Rock,Singer-Songwriter
