 v.1758050806.jpg
CATEGORIES:Theatre Arts
DESCRIPTION:This musical adaptation of Thornton Wilder's hit play The Matc
 hmaker includes humor\, romance\, energetic dance\, and some of the greate
 st songs in music theatre history.  The romantic and comic exploits of Dol
 ly Gallagher Levi\, turn-of-the-century matchmaker and "woman who arranges
  things\," are a thrill and highly entertaining to audiences.  Directed by
  Gina Alvarado  Book by Michael Stewart  Music and Lyrics by Jerry Herman 
  &#160\;  Location: Main Stage Theatre at Burbank Auditorium on Santa Rosa
  Campus.  Tickets: $15  &#160\;Buy tickets here! (https://srjc.universityt
 ickets.com/w/event.aspx?id=1783)  SRJC Theatre Arts Website: https://theat
 rearts.santarosa.edu/ (https://theatrearts.santarosa.edu/)&#160\;
