CATEGORIES:Department Events,District Events
DESCRIPTION:We are excited to share that the selected Keynote Speaker is P
 risca Dorcas Mojica Rodríguez. (https://www.priscadorcas.com/bio/) Prisca
  Dorcas Mojica Rodriguez is a writer\, organizer\, and public intellectual
  whose work centers on the lived experiences of undocumented and formerly 
 undocumented Latine communities. Through powerful storytelling and incisiv
 e cultural critique\, she challenges dominant narratives about immigration
 \, belonging\, and identity in the United States.  Tell us you are coming 
 by submitting your RSVP here (https://santarosajuniorcollege.formstack.com
 /forms/form_1__we_the_future_registration_2026)!  For more information\, v
 isit SRJC's We the Future Website (https://wethefuture.santarosa.edu/)!
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T174832Z
LOCATION:Petaluma Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/we-the-future-2026
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  We are excited to share that the selecte
 d Keynote Speaker is <a href="https://www.priscadorcas.com/bio/">Prisca Do
 rcas Mojica Rodríguez.</a> Prisca Dorcas Mojica Rodriguez is a writer\, o
 rganizer\, and public intellectual whose work centers on the lived experie
 nces of undocumented and formerly undocumented Latine communities. Through
  powerful storytelling and incisive cultural critique\, she challenges dom
 inant narratives about immigration\, belonging\, and identity in the Unite
 d States.</p><p>  Tell us you are coming by submitting your <a href="https
 ://santarosajuniorcollege.formstack.com/forms/form_1__we_the_future_regist
 ration_2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RSVP here</a>!</p><p>  For mor
 e information\, visit <a href="https://wethefuture.santarosa.edu/" target=
 "_blank" rel="noopener">SRJC's We the Future Website</a>!</p>
