SUMMARY:The Calder Quartet - SRJC's Chamber Concert Series
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T170000
DTSTAMP:20250912T154620Z
UID:20260426T230000Z-10045@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/3/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,2000,2000/450_The_Calder_Quartet_-_SRJCs_Chamber_Con
 cert_Series_Calendar.rev.1757717141.png
CATEGORIES:Music
DESCRIPTION:Hailed as "superb" and "imaginative\, skillful creators" by th
 e New York Times\, the Calder Quartet captivates audiences\, exploring a b
 road spectrum of repertoire\, always striving to fulfill the composer's vi
 sion in its performances. The group's distinctive artistry is exemplified 
 by a musical curiosity brought to everything they perform and has led them
  to be called "one of America's most satisfying–and most enterprising–
 quartets."  Winners of the prestigious 2014 Avery Fisher Career Grant\, th
 ey are widely known for the discovery\, commissioning\, recording and ment
 oring of some of today's best emerging composers.  Benjamin Jacobson\, vio
 lin\; Tereza Stanislav\, violin\; Jonathan Moerschel\, viola\; and Eric By
 ers\, cello  &#160\;  Program:  Philip Glass\, String Quartet No. 2\, "Com
 pany"  Ben Johnston\, String Quartet No. 4\, "Amazing Grace"  Samuel Barbe
 r\, String Quartet in B minor Op. 11  Andrew Norman\, Sabrina (arr. for st
 ring quartet)  Florence Price\, String Quartet No. 2*Reception immediately
  following concert  &#160\;  Ticket Prices:  Season tickets (all 6 concert
 s): $155  Mini Season (any 3 concerts): $90  Individual tickets: $35  Stud
 ent tickets (with valid ID): $20  &#160\;Buy tickets here! (https://www.ci
 tyboxoffice.com/?category=36)  SRJC Chamber Concerts Website: https://cham
 berconcerts.santarosa.edu/ (https://chamberconcerts.santarosa.edu/)&#160\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20251202T202928Z
LOCATION:Glaser Center\, 547 Mendocino Avenue Santa Rosa CA
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/10045-the-calder-quartet-srjcs-ch
 amber-concert-series
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Hailed as "superb" and "imaginative\, sk
 illful creators" by the New York Times\, the Calder Quartet captivates aud
 iences\, exploring a broad spectrum of repertoire\, always striving to ful
 fill the composer's vision in its performances. The group's distinctive ar
 tistry is exemplified by a musical curiosity brought to everything they pe
 rform and has led them to be called "one of America's most satisfying–an
 d most enterprising–quartets."<br />  Winners of the prestigious 2014 Av
 ery Fisher Career Grant\, they are widely known for the discovery\, commis
 sioning\, recording and mentoring of some of today's best emerging compose
 rs.</p><p>  Benjamin Jacobson\, violin\; Tereza Stanislav\, violin\; Jonat
 han Moerschel\, viola\; and Eric Byers\, cello</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p>  Pro
 gram:<br />  Philip Glass\, String Quartet No. 2\, "Company"<br />  Ben Jo
 hnston\, String Quartet No. 4\, "Amazing Grace"<br />  Samuel Barber\, Str
 ing Quartet in B minor Op. 11<br />  Andrew Norman\, Sabrina (arr. for str
 ing quartet)<br />  Florence Price\, String Quartet No. 2</p><p><em>*Recep
 tion immediately following concert</em></p><p>  &#160\;</p><p>  Ticket Pri
 ces:<br />  Season tickets (all 6 concerts): $155<br />  Mini Season (any 
 3 concerts): $90<br />  Individual tickets: $35<br />  Student tickets (wi
 th valid ID): $20</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><a href="https://www.cityboxoffice
 .com/?category=36" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy tickets here!</a></p
 ><p>  SRJC Chamber Concerts Website: <a href="https://chamberconcerts.sant
 arosa.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://chamberconcerts.santaro
 sa.edu/</a>&#160\;</p>
